FBIS3-23445 "jptot013__l94126" JPRS-TOT-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 19 March 1994 WEST EUROPE CYPRUS Four Foreigners Arrested Near Bombed Mosque in Nicosia NC1903123994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1000 GMT 19 Mar 94 NC1903123994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] This afternoon, police will bring to Nicosia District Court four foreign students who were arrested late last night in the yard of Omeriye Mosque in Nicosia. [see item NC1603200294 in previous Terrorism Report] The four are Salah-al-Din Billu from Syria, (Usuani Uushtag) from Pakistan, (Larren Fernandes) from India and Ghassan Muhammad from Lebanon. The four students had entered the yard of Omeriye Mosque in a stolen car, which belongs to a resident of Aradhippou village, with fake license plates from a motorcycle. In their possession police found tools used for burglaries and other items, which police are checking on to see if they are stolen.
